command line flags-

dart --help 
for every commands

1. create a new file in empty directory by-
dart$ dart create -t console simple . --force

it will create file in the bin directory of same name as your empty folder
it will make a starter app in vs, here, develop.dart
"develop" is name of my folder name

2. run the program
$ dart run

3. compile it on different targets
(i) .exe
$ dart compile exe bin <name of file>.dart

it will make a .exe file in the directory

to run it-
$ bin/<name of the file>.exe

(ii) .js
$ dart compile js bin <name of the file>.dart

it will make an out.js file

to run it-
$node out.js



